            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19859",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=natew",
                        "name": "natew",
                        "displayName": "Nathan Wright",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Working patch",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=natew",
                        "name": "natew",
                        "displayName": "Nathan Wright",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-11T16:58:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-11T16:58:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19896",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=natew",
                        "name": "natew",
                        "displayName": "Nathan Wright",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This improvement will be useful where the label decorator isn't appropriate. For example, sometimes the label isn't desired immediately before or after the form element, and placement from within a view script or view script decorator is the simplest way to go. It will also be useful for those who aren't using decorators at all.\n\nHere's a unit test (please let me know if this needs improvement in any way, this is a learning process for me):\n{code}    public function testZendFormElementInteroperability()\n    {\n        require_once 'Zend\/Form\/Element.php';\n        $element = new Zend_Form_Element('foo', array('disableLoadDefaultDecorators' => true));\n        $element->setLabel('bar');\n        \n        $label = '<label for=\"foo\">bar<\/label>';\n        $this->assertEquals($this->helper->formLabel($element), $label);\n    }{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=natew",
                        "name": "natew",
                        "displayName": "Nathan Wright",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-12T18:15:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-12T18:15:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20258",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please categorize\/fix as needed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-25T20:33:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-25T20:33:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20517",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I am inclined to say that at current, making the form*() helpers Zend_Form aware is not a level of coupling that we would like to see implemented without fully exploring all the possibilities.\n\nSomething on this magnitude should be proposed through the proposal process.  B\/c if we are gonna do it to one form view helper, then we must do it to all form view helpers.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-28T11:10:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-28T11:10:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21320",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Scheduling for next minor release.\n\nAny solution should address all form helpers, as Ralph suggests, to ensure that we have a consistent story for using view helpers with form objects.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-22T11:26:50.000+0000",
